  Did you mean 'List<String> vcsurl = new ArrayList<>();'?

FROM ubi8-minimal:8.3-298.1618432845
USER root
ENV CHE_HOME=/home/user/codeready
ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/jre
RUN microdnf install java-11-openjdk-headless tar gzip shadow-utils findutils && \
    microdnf update -y gnutls && \
    microdnf -y clean all && rm -rf /var/cache/yum && echo "Installed Packages" && rpm -qa | sort -V && echo "End Of Installed Packages" && \
    adduser -G root user && mkdir -p /home/user/codeready
COPY entrypoint.sh /entrypoint.sh
ENTRYPOINT ["/entrypoint.sh"]
# NOTE: To build in Brew, use get-sources-jenkins.sh to build new server.tgz
COPY asset-server.tgz /tmp/asset-server.tgz
RUN tar xzf /tmp/asset-server.tgz --strip-components=1 -C /home/user/codeready; rm -f /tmp/asset-server.tgz
# this should fail if the startup script is not found in correct path /home/user/codeready/tomcat/bin/catalina.sh
RUN mkdir /logs /data && \
    chmod 0777 /logs /data && \
    chgrp -R 0 /home/user /logs /data && \
    chown -R user /home/user && \
    chmod -R g+rwX /home/user && \
    find /home/user -type d -exec chmod 777 {} \; && \
    java -version && echo -n "Server startup script in: " && \
    find /home/user/codeready -name catalina.sh | grep -z /home/user/codeready/tomcat/bin/catalina.sh
USER user

# Copyright (c) 2018-2020 Red Hat, Inc.

# https://access.redhat.com/containers/?tab=tags#/registry.access.redhat.com/ubi8-minimal
FROM sha256:88b7feca21692b223bbfc4e12eb4de0f39aab52f114b767e159dcc1d6a14cc1e
RUN mv -f /etc/yum.repos.d/ubi.repo /tmp || :
ADD tls-ca-bundle.pem /tmp/tls-ca-bundle.pem
ADD atomic-reactor-repos/* /etc/yum.repos.d/
USER root
ENV CHE_HOME=/home/user/codeready
ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/jre
RUN microdnf install java-11-openjdk-headless tar gzip shadow-utils findutils && \
    microdnf update -y gnutls && \
    microdnf -y clean all && rm -rf /var/cache/yum && echo "Installed Packages" && rpm -qa | sort -V && echo "End Of Installed Packages" && \
    adduser -G root user && mkdir -p /home/user/codeready
COPY entrypoint.sh /entrypoint.sh
ENTRYPOINT ["/entrypoint.sh"]

# NOTE: To build in Brew, use get-sources-jenkins.sh to build new server.tgz
COPY asset-server.tgz /tmp/asset-server.tgz
RUN tar xzf /tmp/asset-server.tgz --strip-components=1 -C /home/user/codeready; rm -f /tmp/asset-server.tgz

# this should fail if the startup script is not found in correct path /home/user/codeready/tomcat/bin/catalina.sh
RUN mkdir /logs /data && \
    chmod 0777 /logs /data && \
    chgrp -R 0 /home/user /logs /data && \
    chown -R user /home/user && \
    chmod -R g+rwX /home/user && \
    find /home/user -type d -exec chmod 777 {} \; && \
    java -version && echo -n "Server startup script in: " && \
    find /home/user/codeready -name catalina.sh | grep -z /home/user/codeready/tomcat/bin/catalina.sh

USER user

# append Brew metadata here
ENV SUMMARY="Red Hat CodeReady Workspaces server container" \
    DESCRIPTION="Red Hat CodeReady Workspaces server container" \
    PRODNAME="codeready-workspaces" \
    COMPNAME="server-rhel8"
LABEL summary="$SUMMARY" \
      description="$DESCRIPTION" \
      io.k8s.description="$DESCRIPTION" \
      io.k8s.display-name="$DESCRIPTION" \
      io.openshift.tags="$PRODNAME,$COMPNAME" \
      com.redhat.component="$PRODNAME-$COMPNAME-container" \
      name="$PRODNAME/$COMPNAME" \
      version="2.9" \
      license="EPLv2" \
      maintainer="Nick Boldt <nboldt@redhat.com>" \
      io.openshift.expose-services="" \
      usage=""

ADD codeready-workspaces-server-rhel8-container-2.9-6.json /root/buildinfo/content_manifests/codeready-workspaces-server-rhel8-container-2.9-6.json
ADD Dockerfile-codeready-workspaces-server-rhel8-2.9-6 /root/buildinfo/Dockerfile-codeready-workspaces-server-rhel8-2.9-6
LABEL "release"="6" "com.redhat.license_terms"="https://www.redhat.com/agreements" "distribution-scope"="public" "vendor"="Red Hat, Inc." "build-date"="2021-05-14T00:11:42.884236" "architecture"="ppc64le" "vcs-type"="git" "vcs-ref"="26b1c16a25f401b26f5ed4c7acab821fb3c9ec75" "com.redhat.build-host"="ppc64le-c1-vm-04.prod.osbs.eng.rdu2.redhat.com" "url"="https://access.redhat.com/containers/#/registry.access.redhat.com/codeready-workspaces/server-rhel8/images/2.9-6"
USER root
RUN rm -f '/etc/yum.repos.d/odcs-703964-5a091.repo'
RUN rm -f /tmp/tls-ca-bundle.pem
USER user
USER root
RUN mv -fZ /tmp/ubi.repo /etc/yum.repos.d/ubi.repo || :

# Copyright (c) 2018-2020 Red Hat, Inc.
# This program and the accompanying materials are made

# https://access.redhat.com/containers/?tab=tags#/registry.access.redhat.com/ubi8-minimal
FROM sha256:332744c1854d8e87f41dc67bf3d7e1c08d7a6b1322b5b5bd0b126bf8282ca1f8
RUN mv -f /etc/yum.repos.d/ubi.repo /tmp || :
ADD tls-ca-bundle.pem /tmp/tls-ca-bundle.pem
ADD atomic-reactor-repos/* /etc/yum.repos.d/
USER root
ENV CHE_HOME=/home/user/codeready
ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/jre
RUN microdnf install java-11-openjdk-headless tar gzip shadow-utils findutils && \
    microdnf update -y gnutls && \
    microdnf -y clean all && rm -rf /var/cache/yum && echo "Installed Packages" && rpm -qa | sort -V && echo "End Of Installed Packages" && \
    adduser -G root user && mkdir -p /home/user/codeready
COPY entrypoint.sh /entrypoint.sh
ENTRYPOINT ["/entrypoint.sh"]

# NOTE: To build in Brew, use get-sources-jenkins.sh to build new server.tgz
COPY asset-server.tgz /tmp/asset-server.tgz
RUN tar xzf /tmp/asset-server.tgz --strip-components=1 -C /home/user/codeready; rm -f /tmp/asset-server.tgz

# this should fail if the startup script is not found in correct path /home/user/codeready/tomcat/bin/catalina.sh
RUN mkdir /logs /data && \
    chmod 0777 /logs /data && \
    chgrp -R 0 /home/user /logs /data && \
    chown -R user /home/user && \
    chmod -R g+rwX /home/user && \
    find /home/user -type d -exec chmod 777 {} \; && \
    java -version && echo -n "Server startup script in: " && \
    find /home/user/codeready -name catalina.sh | grep -z /home/user/codeready/tomcat/bin/catalina.sh

USER user

# append Brew metadata here
ENV SUMMARY="Red Hat CodeReady Workspaces server container" \
    DESCRIPTION="Red Hat CodeReady Workspaces server container" \
    PRODNAME="codeready-workspaces" \
    COMPNAME="server-rhel8"
LABEL summary="$SUMMARY" \
      description="$DESCRIPTION" \
      io.k8s.description="$DESCRIPTION" \
      io.k8s.display-name="$DESCRIPTION" \
      io.openshift.tags="$PRODNAME,$COMPNAME" \
      com.redhat.component="$PRODNAME-$COMPNAME-container" \
      name="$PRODNAME/$COMPNAME" \
      version="2.9" \
      license="EPLv2" \
      maintainer="Nick Boldt <nboldt@redhat.com>" \
      io.openshift.expose-services="" \
      usage=""

ADD codeready-workspaces-server-rhel8-container-2.9-6.json /root/buildinfo/content_manifests/codeready-workspaces-server-rhel8-container-2.9-6.json
ADD Dockerfile-codeready-workspaces-server-rhel8-2.9-6 /root/buildinfo/Dockerfile-codeready-workspaces-server-rhel8-2.9-6
LABEL "release"="6" "com.redhat.license_terms"="https://www.redhat.com/agreements" "distribution-scope"="public" "vendor"="Red Hat, Inc." "build-date"="2021-05-14T00:12:46.669410" "architecture"="x86_64" "vcs-type"="git" "vcs-ref"="26b1c16a25f401b26f5ed4c7acab821fb3c9ec75" "com.redhat.build-host"="cpt-1002.osbs.prod.upshift.rdu2.redhat.com" "url"="https://access.redhat.com/containers/#/registry.access.redhat.com/codeready-workspaces/server-rhel8/images/2.9-6"
USER root
RUN rm -f '/etc/yum.repos.d/odcs-703962-e76e0.repo'
RUN rm -f /tmp/tls-ca-bundle.pem
USER user

RUN mv -fZ /tmp/ubi.repo /etc/yum.repos.d/ubi.repo || :

# https://access.redhat.com/containers/?tab=tags#/registry.access.redhat.com/ubi8-minimal
FROM sha256:1264d9863dfd9bedef87ff83d69e194ccdbf2b636d78284d2379cdd3e0d54eff
RUN mv -f /etc/yum.repos.d/ubi.repo /tmp || :
ADD tls-ca-bundle.pem /tmp/tls-ca-bundle.pem
ADD atomic-reactor-repos/* /etc/yum.repos.d/
USER root
ENV CHE_HOME=/home/user/codeready
ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/jre
RUN microdnf install java-11-openjdk-headless tar gzip shadow-utils findutils && \
    microdnf update -y gnutls && \
    microdnf -y clean all && rm -rf /var/cache/yum && echo "Installed Packages" && rpm -qa | sort -V && echo "End Of Installed Packages" && \
    adduser -G root user && mkdir -p /home/user/codeready
COPY entrypoint.sh /entrypoint.sh
ENTRYPOINT ["/entrypoint.sh"]

# NOTE: To build in Brew, use get-sources-jenkins.sh to build new server.tgz
COPY asset-server.tgz /tmp/asset-server.tgz
RUN tar xzf /tmp/asset-server.tgz --strip-components=1 -C /home/user/codeready; rm -f /tmp/asset-server.tgz

# this should fail if the startup script is not found in correct path /home/user/codeready/tomcat/bin/catalina.sh
RUN mkdir /logs /data && \
    chmod 0777 /logs /data && \
    chgrp -R 0 /home/user /logs /data && \
    chown -R user /home/user && \
    chmod -R g+rwX /home/user && \
    find /home/user -type d -exec chmod 777 {} \; && \
    java -version && echo -n "Server startup script in: " && \
    find /home/user/codeready -name catalina.sh | grep -z /home/user/codeready/tomcat/bin/catalina.sh

USER user

# append Brew metadata here

    PRODNAME="codeready-workspaces" \
    COMPNAME="server-rhel8"

      description="$DESCRIPTION" \

      com.redhat.component="$PRODNAME-$COMPNAME-container" \

      license="EPLv2" \

# https://access.redhat.com/containers/?tab=tags#/registry.access.redhat.com/ubi8-minimal
FROM ubi8-minimal:8.3-298.1618432845
USER root
ENV CHE_HOME=/home/user/codeready
ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/jre
RUN microdnf install java-11-openjdk-headless tar gzip shadow-utils findutils && \
    microdnf update -y gnutls && \
    microdnf -y clean all && rm -rf /var/cache/yum && echo "Installed Packages" && rpm -qa | sort -V && echo "End Of Installed Packages" && \
    adduser -G root user && mkdir -p /home/user/codeready
COPY entrypoint.sh /entrypoint.sh
ENTRYPOINT ["/entrypoint.sh"]

# NOTE: To build in Brew, use get-sources-jenkins.sh to build new server.tgz
COPY asset-server.tgz /tmp/asset-server.tgz
RUN tar xzf /tmp/asset-server.tgz --strip-components=1 -C /home/user/codeready; rm -f /tmp/asset-server.tgz

# this should fail if the startup script is not found in correct path /home/user/codeready/tomcat/bin/catalina.sh
RUN mkdir /logs /data && \
    chmod 0777 /logs /data && \
    chgrp -R 0 /home/user /logs /data && \
    chown -R user /home/user && \
    chmod -R g+rwX /home/user && \
    find /home/user -type d -exec chmod 777 {} \; && \
    java -version && echo -n "Server startup script in: " && \
    find /home/user/codeready -name catalina.sh | grep -z /home/user/codeready/tomcat/bin/catalina.sh

USER user

# append Brew metadata here
ENV SUMMARY="Red Hat CodeReady Workspaces server container" \
    DESCRIPTION="Red Hat CodeReady Workspaces server container" \
    PRODNAME="codeready-workspaces" \
    COMPNAME="server-rhel8"

# https://access.redhat.com/containers/?tab=tags#/registry.access.redhat.com/ubi8-minimal
FROM ubi8-minimal:8.3-298.1618432845
USER root
ENV CHE_HOME=/home/user/codeready
ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/jre
RUN microdnf install java-11-openjdk-headless tar gzip shadow-utils findutils && \
    microdnf update -y gnutls && \
    microdnf -y clean all && rm -rf /var/cache/yum && echo "Installed Packages" && rpm -qa | sort -V && echo "End Of Installed Packages" && \
    adduser -G root user && mkdir -p /home/user/codeready
COPY entrypoint.sh /entrypoint.sh
ENTRYPOINT ["/entrypoint.sh"]

# NOTE: To build in Brew, use get-sources-jenkins.sh to build new server.tgz
COPY asset-server.tgz /tmp/asset-server.tgz
RUN tar xzf /tmp/asset-server.tgz --strip-components=1 -C /home/user/codeready; rm -f /tmp/asset-server.tgz

# this should fail if the startup script is not found in correct path /home/user/codeready/tomcat/bin/catalina.sh
RUN mkdir /logs /data && \
    chmod 0777 /logs /data && \
    chgrp -R 0 /home/user /logs /data && \
    chown -R user /home/user && \
    chmod -R g+rwX /home/user && \
    find /home/user -type d -exec chmod 777 {} \; && \
    java -version && echo -n "Server startup script in: " && \
    find /home/user/codeready -name catalina.sh | grep -z /home/user/codeready/tomcat/bin/catalina.sh

USER user

# append Brew metadata here
ENV SUMMARY="Red Hat CodeReady Workspaces server container" \
    DESCRIPTION="Red Hat CodeReady Workspaces server container" \
    PRODNAME="codeready-workspaces" \
    COMPNAME="server-rhel8"
LABEL summary="$SUMMARY" \
      description="$DESCRIPTION" \
      io.k8s.description="$DESCRIPTION" \
      io.k8s.display-name="$DESCRIPTION" \
      io.openshift.tags="$PRODNAME,$COMPNAME" \
      com.redhat.component="$PRODNAME-$COMPNAME-container" \
      name="$PRODNAME/$COMPNAME" \
      version="2.9" \
      license="EPLv2" \
      maintainer="Nick Boldt <nboldt@redhat.com>" \
      io.openshift.expose-services="" \
      usage=""

# https://access.redhat.com/containers/?tab=tags#/registry.access.redhat.com/ubi8-minimal
FROM ubi8-minimal:8.3-298.1618432845
USER root
ENV CHE_HOME=/home/user/codeready
ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/jre
RUN microdnf install java-11-openjdk-headless tar gzip shadow-utils findutils && \
    microdnf update -y gnutls && \
    microdnf -y clean all && rm -rf /var/cache/yum && echo "Installed Packages" && rpm -qa | sort -V && echo "End Of Installed Packages" && \
    adduser -G root user && mkdir -p /home/user/codeready
COPY entrypoint.sh /entrypoint.sh
ENTRYPOINT ["/entrypoint.sh"]

# NOTE: To build in Brew, use get-sources-jenkins.sh to build new server.tgz
COPY asset-server.tgz /tmp/asset-server.tgz
RUN tar xzf /tmp/asset-server.tgz --strip-components=1 -C /home/user/codeready; rm -f /tmp/asset-server.tgz

# this should fail if the startup script is not found in correct path /home/user/codeready/tomcat/bin/catalina.sh
RUN mkdir /logs /data && \
    chmod 0777 /logs /data && \
    chgrp -R 0 /home/user /logs /data && \
    chown -R user /home/user && \
    chmod -R g+rwX /home/user && \
    find /home/user -type d -exec chmod 777 {} \; && \
    java -version && echo -n "Server startup script in: " && \
    find /home/user/codeready -name catalina.sh | grep -z /home/user/codeready/tomcat/bin/catalina.sh

USER user

# append Brew metadata here
ENV SUMMARY="Red Hat CodeReady Workspaces server container" \
    DESCRIPTION="Red Hat CodeReady Workspaces server container" \
    PRODNAME="codeready-workspaces" \
    COMPNAME="server-rhel8"

      description="$DESCRIPTION" \
